{
  "text": "Eradication of infection was achieved in 82.3 -100% with EF, 71.4 -100% with IMN, 85.5% with dual plating [CITATION_1] and 100% with cannulated screws [CITATION_2] . Independent mobility (with walking aids) reached 100% in all fixation methods. Pain relief reached 100% with EF [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] whereas this was variable with IMN as reported rates of residual pain reached as high as 62% despite complete union [CITATION_5] . Arthrodesis using cannulated screws produced significant improvement in pain scores [CITATION_6] .",
